title: First-timers Wemby, Sengun top All-Star reserves
description: The Spurs' Victor Wembanyama and the Rockets' Alperen Sengun were among six first-timers named to the NBA All-Star Game on Thursday, when the league announced the reserves.
author: Tim Bontemps

title: Ravens' Tucker accused of inappropriate behavior
description: Six massage therapists in the Baltimore area have accused Ravens kicker Justin Tucker of inappropriate sexual behavior between 2012 and 2016, according to a report.
author: Jamison Hensley

title: Coote: I felt ashamed; they were dark days
description: David Coote says he feels "ashamed" of the incidents which led to him being sacked by the Professional Game Match Officials Limited (PGMOL) and has reflected on the "dark" days he experienced as stories about him emerged, in an interview with Sky Sports.

title: No defence for Sanchez's errors at Chelsea - despite the data
description: When Chelsea were on a run of eight consecutive wins last month, there was still a nagging suspicion that they were lacking in key areas and that it could cost them. The best teams have a top-class striker and a top-class goalkeeper, so the theory goes.

title: 'Spurs don't need to buy anyone - just play the kids'
description: Ange Postecoglou says the 3-0 Europa League win over Elfsborg was "made in Tottenham" as youngsters Dane Scarlett, Damola Ajayi and Mikey Moore all score.

title: How Rangers and Europa League seem made for each other
description: Finalists in 2022 and now back in the knockout stages despite their domestic difficulties - the Europa League is Rangers' happy place.

title: NBA announces All-Star reserves with Wemby making team for 1st time
description: The second-year superstar has earned the first of what is expected to be a long line of All-Star honors. Here's a look at all the reserves.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: From awkward to outrageous: 10 memorably infamous coaching press conferences
description: Liam Coen's awkward introduction as Jaguars coach joins a list of press conferences remembered for the wrong reasons.
author: Yahoo Sports
